All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
App
App is the top-level class for the Aquarium simulation.
Bubble
Sets-up and controls Bubble objects.
BubbleEvent
Interface: Allows objects to communicate with the bubble factory to spawn bubbles.
BubbleFactory
Factory that creates bubbles for any class that has a reference to BubbleEvent.
IUpdatable
Interface: Updates object - to be called on each cycle of the simulation.
JavaFish
Sets-up and controls JavaFish objects.
NullTextureException
Exception thrown if there is an error with texture assignment.
OutOfBoundsException
Exception thrown if a pet is created outside the bounds of the window.
PetFactory
Class for pet creation.
Piranha
Sets-up and controls Piranha objects.
Seahorse
Sets-up and controls Seahorse objects.
Urchin
Sets-up and controls urchin objects.
Window
Window enumerator that specifies the dimensions of the window.
